#: src/gedcom_strings.py:144
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"Reverse ({mod}R)\n"
"Reverse the direction of all relationship paths shown, computing the "
"relationship from the other person's perspective. Click again to restore "
"the original path."
msgstr ""

#: src/gedcom_strings.py:157
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"Copy results ({mod}C)\n"
"Copy the entire contents of the results pane to the clipboard. When the "
"results text area has keyboard focus, {mod}C copies only the selected "
"text as usual."
msgstr ""

#: src/gedcom_strings.py:167
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"Copy JSON ({mod}J)\n"
"Copy the entire contents of the results pane as JSON to the clipboard. "
"Used only for debugging."
msgstr ""

#: src/gedcom_strings.py:175
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"Save ({mod}S)\n"
"Save the results using the format selected in Preferences."
msgstr ""

#: src/gedcom_strings.py:182
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"Find ({mod}F)\n"
"Type to filter the list of people. Search by any name variation. Use the "
"filter box to search by other information in a person's GEDCOM record, "
"such as geographic location or occupation. Press Enter to jump directly "
"to the first match. Use the checkboxes to show only people matching tags,"
" allow fuzzy name matching (including Cyrillic and Hebrew characters), or"
" include married names."
msgstr ""

#: src/gedcom_strings.py:194
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"Bio ({mod}B)\n"
"Show the biographical profile for the selected person."
msgstr ""

#: src/gedcom_strings.py:202
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"Pedigree ({display})\n"
"Show an Ahnentafel ancestor report for the selected person, listing "
"ancestors by generation with numbered entries."
msgstr ""

#: src/gedcom_strings.py:211
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"Descendants ({display})\n"
"Show a Henry-numbered descendant report for the selected person, listing "
"all descendants with their spouses."
msgstr ""

#: src/gedcom_strings.py:220
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"Matches ({mod}N)\n"
"Show the closest tagged matches to the selected person. The results are "
"ranked by proximity to the selected person, with ties broken by the "
"number of tags (if any) associated with the match. Use the 'Results' and "
"'Max Depth' settings to adjust how many results are returned and how far "
"to search within the tree."
msgstr ""

#: src/gedcom_strings.py:232
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"Filter ({mod}I)\n"
"Type to filter the list of people by any information in their GEDCOM "
"record, such as geographic location or occupation. This filter is applied"
" in addition to the Find box above."
msgstr ""

#: src/gedcom_strings.py:240
msgid ""
"Enter a keyword to filter the list of tags used for finding relationship "
"paths. Leave this blank to use only the page marker keyword to find "
"relationship paths."
msgstr ""

#: src/gedcom_strings.py:244
msgid ""
"Enter a unique keyword to use as a page marker when finding relationship "
"paths. Leave this blank to use only the tag keyword to find relationship "
"paths."
msgstr ""

#: src/gedcom_strings.py:252
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"Set Home Person ({display})\n"
"Set the selected person as the home person for finding relationship "
"paths. Select the current home person to unset it."
msgstr ""

#: src/gedcom_strings.py:259
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"Profile ({mod}B)\n"
"Show the selected person's biographical, family, tag, and optional full "
"GEDCOM record details in the Display Pane."
msgstr ""

#: src/gedcom_strings.py:266
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"Tree View ({mod}E)\n"
"Open the configured default tree view for the selected person."
msgstr ""

#: src/gedcom_strings.py:273
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"Select tag for Finding Matches ({mod}T)\n"
"Select a tag (e.g. 'DNA') to use when finding closest matches for the "
"selected person."
msgstr ""

#: src/gedcom_strings.py:281
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"Paths ({mod}P)\n"
"Show relationship paths between the selected person and a target person. "
"The first time you enter Paths mode, choose the target person."
msgstr ""

#: src/gedcom_strings.py:287
msgid ""
"Number of Results\n"
"Specify how many results to return when finding the closest people who "
"are tagged as well as the number of paths between the selected person and"
" the home person."
msgstr ""

#: src/gedcom_strings.py:293
msgid ""
"Maximum Depth For Finding Relationships\n"
"Specify how far to search within the tree for tagged matches and "
"relationship paths between two people. Higher values will find more "
"distant connections but will take longer to find in large trees. "
"Reasonable values are 10 for fast searching or 50 to find extremely "
"distant but often interesting paths between people in your tree. To "
"change this setting permanently, alter it in the preferences window."
msgstr ""

#: src/gedcom_strings.py:303
msgid ""
"Fuzzy Threshold\n"
"Similarity cutoff for fuzzy name search, from 0.00 to 1.00 (default "
"0.72). Lower values allow more matches; higher values are stricter."
msgstr ""

#: src/gedcom_strings.py:308
msgid ""
"Maximum Search Results\n"
"Maximum number of people shown in the search results list. Higher values "
"may slow down filtering in very large trees."
msgstr ""

#: src/gedcom_strings.py:317
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"Toggle Tagged Only ({mod}D)\n"
"When checked, only people flagged as tagged will be shown in search "
"results. Default Tags are DNA-related, but you can set other tag terms. "
"Default is unchecked to show all people, but checking this focuses on "
"tagged matches in large trees."
msgstr ""

#: src/gedcom_strings.py:326
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"Toggle Fuzzy Search ({mod}U)\n"
"Allow fuzzy name matching in search results. Fuzzy matching uses a "
"similarity ratio to find names similar to the search term, which can help"
" find matches when names are misspelled, have minor variations, or use "
"cached Hebrew/Cyrillic transliterated aliases."
msgstr ""

#: src/gedcom_strings.py:336
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"Toggle Married Names ({display})\n"
"Include women's married names in Find searches by combining each woman's "
"given name with the last names of her husbands."
msgstr ""

